```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

The CSS rule centers a div both horizontally and vertically using flexbox. The `container` class should be applied to the parent element that contains the div you want to center. `display: flex` enables flexbox, `justify-content: center` centers the content horizontally, and `align-items: center` centers the content vertically. The `height: 100vh` ensures the container takes up the full viewport height, which is necessary for vertical centering.

